rComments: Lecture slides are very detailed and thorough, and always posted before class. Lectures are heavy and there's usually no break for two hours, so reading beforehand will be extremely helpful to keep the lecture pace. He does a great explanation of lecture materials and is very approachable outside the class if there are any questions.

Great prof! Lectures are clear and easy to understand, very approachable in class and in office hours. The three assignments are relatively straightforward but takes quite some time. Overall the course is designed that if you put in time and effort, you will have a decent grade.
Very pleased with having him. He is very welcoming and helpful during office hours. Absolutely loved the course!
